text: Jahkeele Marshall-Rutty (born June 16, 2004) is a Canadian soccer player who plays as a forward for Toronto FC in MLS. == Club career == === Youth === Marshall-Rutty began playing for Toronto FC Academy in the USSDA in the 2016–2017 season, playing for the U13 team. He has since played for the U15, U16/17 and U18/19 teams as well. === Toronto FC II === Marshall-Rutty signed with Toronto FC II on December 17, 2018, becoming the youngest homegrown player to sign with the club. He made his professional debut for Toronto FC II in USL League One on June 28, 2019, coming on as an 86th minute substitute for Jordan Faria against Forward Madison FC. === Toronto FC === Marshall-Rutty moved to Toronto FC's MLS side on January 22, 2020. He became the youngest player to sign a first-team contract with the club at age 15. == International career == === Youth === ==== Under-15 ==== Marshall-Rutty received his first international call-up to the Canada national under-15 team for the 2019 CONCACAF Boys' Under-15 Championship. == References == == External links == * Toronto FC player profile * Canada Soccer player profile * Category:2004 births Category:Living people Category:Toronto FC II players Category:USL League One players Category:Toronto FC players Category:Canada men's youth international soccer players Category:Sportspeople from Brampton Category:Soccer people from Ontario Category:Canadian soccer players Category:Association football forwards Category:Homegrown Players (MLS)
